body_html:
hi, if you just load image in vgg16 , it is work. but I need to "transfer learning" so I download about 30000 images. You can copy my all the code and run.
there have a weird thing !!! this problem will not happen in inception_v3.

img = tf.keras.applications.vgg16.preprocess_input(img) 
==>img = tf.keras.applications.inception_v3.preprocess_input(img


img = tf.image.resize_images(img, (224, 224))
==>img = tf.image.resize_images(img, (299, 299))

image_model = tf.keras.applications.vgg16.VGG16(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')
==>image_model = tf.keras.applications.InceptionV3(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')

you just change above 3 codes the problem was solved. but it very weird.

body:
hi, if you just load image in vgg16 , it is work. but I need to "transfer learning" so I download about 30000 images. You can copy my all the code and run. 
there have a weird thing !!! this problem will not happen in inception_v3. 
```
img = tf.keras.applications.vgg16.preprocess_input(img) 
==>img = tf.keras.applications.inception_v3.preprocess_input(img
```
```

img = tf.image.resize_images(img, (224, 224))
==>img = tf.image.resize_images(img, (299, 299))
```

```
image_model = tf.keras.applications.vgg16.VGG16(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')
==>image_model = tf.keras.applications.InceptionV3(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')
```
you just change above 3 codes the problem was solved. but it very weird.
